 genre. The existential philosophical Bildungsroman depicts crises of self-presentation, discarding exemplary aspects of character formation in favor of an alternative concept of literary self-awareness.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aEuropean fictiony20th centuryxHistory and criticism. 0aSelf in literature. 4aBildungsroman. 4aGattungstheorie. 4aRomantheorie. 4aSelbstrepräsentation. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh  aGenre theory.  abildungsroman.  aself-representation.  atheory of the novel.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2016 Part 1z978311076250108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2016z978311070100508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2015z9783110439687oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural and Area Studies 2015z9783110438673oZDB-23-DKU0 cEPUBz97831103847270 cprintz978311034837840uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311034869940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110348699423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110348699/original  a978-3-11-070100-5  DG Plus eBook-Package 2016b2016  a978-3-11-076250-1  DG Plus DeG Package 2016 Part 1b2016  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGGb2015  aZDB-23-DKUb2015